# Cursor Rules for JUSTBUILD2.0 Project

## MCP (Model Context Protocol) Configuration

This project supports MCP servers for enhanced AI capabilities. To connect Vercel MCP:

### 1. Deploy Vercel MCP Server
- Deploy the Vercel MCP server to your Vercel account
- Get your deployment URL (e.g., https://your-vercel-mcp.vercel.app/api/mcp)

### 2. Configure in Cursor Settings
1. Open Cursor Settings (Cmd+, on Mac)
2. Navigate to: Features > MCP
3. Click "+ Add New MCP Server"
4. Configure:
   - Name: "Vercel MCP"
   - Type: "Streamable HTTP"
   - URL: Your deployed MCP server URL
5. Save the configuration

### 3. Default MCP Servers in Project
This project already includes a default LangGraph docs MCP server configured in:
- `packages/shared/src/constants.ts` - DEFAULT_MCP_SERVERS
- `packages/shared/src/open-swe/mcp.ts` - MCP configuration schemas

### 4. Custom MCP Servers
You can add custom MCP servers in the web UI settings under the "mcpServers" configuration field as JSON.

## Project Context
- This is a LangGraph-based OpenSWE application
- MCP integration is already built into the codebase
- The project uses TypeScript and Next.js for the web interface
- Authentication is handled via GitHub OAuth

## Key MCP-Related Files
- `apps/open-swe/src/utils/mcp-client.ts` - MCP client implementation
- `apps/open-swe/src/utils/mcp-output/` - MCP output handling
- `packages/shared/src/open-swe/mcp.ts` - MCP type definitions

